name: Post-Workout Protein Pancakes
ingredients: Protein powder (vanilla), oats, egg whites, banana, Greek yogurt, cinnamon, baking powder, almond milk
recipe: 1. Blend oats into flour. 2. Mix protein powder, oat flour, baking powder, cinnamon. 3. Combine egg whites, mashed banana, almond milk. 4. Mix wet and dry ingredients. 5. Cook pancakes in non-stick pan. 6. Top with Greek yogurt.

name: Lean Beef Power Bowl
ingredients: Lean ground beef (93/7), brown rice, sweet potato, spinach, quinoa, bell peppers, olive oil, garlic, onion
recipe: 1. Cook brown rice and quinoa. 2. Roast diced sweet potato. 3. Sauté lean beef with garlic and onion. 4. Steam spinach and bell peppers. 5. Combine all ingredients in bowl. 6. Drizzle with olive oil.

name: Grilled Chicken Meal Prep
ingredients: Chicken breast, jasmine rice, broccoli, asparagus, olive oil, lemon, herbs, garlic powder, paprika
recipe: 1. Season chicken with herbs and spices. 2. Grill chicken breast until cooked through. 3. Steam broccoli and asparagus. 4. Cook jasmine rice. 5. Portion into meal prep containers. 6. Drizzle with lemon and olive oil.

name: Pre-Workout Energy Smoothie
ingredients: Whey protein powder, banana, oats, almond milk, espresso shot, Greek yogurt, honey, ice
recipe: 1. Add all ingredients to blender. 2. Blend until smooth and creamy. 3. Add ice for desired consistency. 4. Consume 30-45 minutes before workout.

name: Salmon Power Plate
ingredients: Atlantic salmon fillet, quinoa, kale, avocado, cherry tomatoes, lemon, olive oil, garlic, almonds
recipe: 1. Season and bake salmon at 400°F for 15 minutes. 2. Cook quinoa with garlic. 3. Massage kale with lemon and olive oil. 4. Slice avocado and halve tomatoes. 5. Plate salmon over quinoa and kale. 6. Top with avocado and almonds.

name: Turkey Meatball Pasta Bowl
ingredients: Lean ground turkey, whole wheat pasta, spinach, marinara sauce, parmesan, egg, breadcrumbs, Italian herbs
recipe: 1. Mix turkey with egg, breadcrumbs, herbs for meatballs. 2. Bake meatballs at 375°F for 20 minutes. 3. Cook whole wheat pasta. 4. Heat marinara sauce. 5. Sauté spinach. 6. Combine all ingredients, top with parmesan.

name: Egg White Protein Scramble
ingredients: Egg whites, whole eggs, spinach, mushrooms, bell peppers, low-fat cheese, cooking spray, herbs
recipe: 1. Spray pan with cooking spray. 2. Sauté vegetables until tender. 3. Pour in egg whites and whole eggs. 4. Scramble until fluffy. 5. Add cheese and herbs. 6. Serve immediately.

name: Tuna Protein Salad
ingredients: Canned tuna in water, mixed greens, chickpeas, cucumber, tomatoes, Greek yogurt, lemon juice, Dijon mustard
recipe: 1. Drain tuna and flake. 2. Mix Greek yogurt with lemon and mustard for dressing. 3. Combine mixed greens, cucumber, tomatoes, chickpeas. 4. Top with tuna. 5. Drizzle with yogurt dressing.

name: Casein Protein Night Bowl
ingredients: Casein protein powder, Greek yogurt, almond butter, berries, chia seeds, vanilla extract, stevia
recipe: 1. Mix casein protein with small amount of water to form paste. 2. Fold in Greek yogurt. 3. Add almond butter and vanilla. 4. Top with berries and chia seeds. 5. Consume before bed for overnight recovery.

name: Lean Steak Performance Meal
ingredients: Sirloin steak (lean cut), sweet potato, green beans, mushrooms, garlic, rosemary, olive oil, balsamic vinegar
recipe: 1. Season steak with garlic and rosemary. 2. Grill steak to desired doneness. 3. Roast sweet potato wedges. 4. Sauté green beans and mushrooms. 5. Let steak rest, then slice. 6. Drizzle with balsamic reduction.

name: Cottage Cheese Power Bowl
ingredients: Low-fat cottage cheese, granola, mixed berries, honey, walnuts, cinnamon, vanilla extract
recipe: 1. Place cottage cheese in bowl. 2. Add vanilla extract and cinnamon. 3. Top with granola and berries. 4. Drizzle with honey. 5. Sprinkle chopped walnuts. 6. Serve immediately.

name: Chicken Protein Wrap
ingredients: Whole wheat tortilla, grilled chicken breast, hummus, lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, feta cheese
recipe: 1. Slice grilled chicken breast. 2. Spread hummus on tortilla. 3. Layer lettuce, tomatoes, cucumber, onion. 4. Add chicken and feta cheese. 5. Roll tightly, securing with toothpick. 6. Cut in half to serve.

name: Post-Workout Recovery Shake
ingredients: Whey protein isolate, banana, white rice (cooked and cooled), coconut water, leucine supplement, ice
recipe: 1. Add all ingredients to blender. 2. Blend until completely smooth. 3. Consume within 30 minutes post-workout for optimal recovery. 4. Add ice for preferred consistency.

name: Quinoa Protein Buddha Bowl
ingredients: Quinoa, black beans, chickpeas, roasted vegetables, tahini, lemon juice, nutritional yeast, pumpkin seeds
recipe: 1. Cook quinoa with vegetable broth. 2. Roast mixed vegetables with herbs. 3. Heat black beans and chickpeas. 4. Make tahini dressing with lemon. 5. Assemble bowl with all components. 6. Sprinkle nutritional yeast and pumpkin seeds.

name: Turkey and Sweet Potato Hash
ingredients: Ground turkey (lean), sweet potato, bell peppers, onion, eggs, spinach, olive oil, paprika, cumin
recipe: 1. Dice and roast sweet potato. 2. Cook ground turkey with spices. 3. Sauté peppers and onion. 4. Combine turkey and vegetables. 5. Create wells and crack eggs into them. 6. Cover until eggs are cooked, add spinach.

name: Greek Yogurt Protein Parfait
ingredients: Greek yogurt (0% fat), protein powder, granola, mixed berries, honey, almonds, chia seeds
recipe: 1. Mix protein powder into Greek yogurt. 2. Layer yogurt mixture with granola in glass. 3. Add layer of mixed berries. 4. Repeat layers. 5. Top with almonds and chia seeds. 6. Drizzle with honey.

name: Baked Cod with Quinoa
ingredients: Cod fillet, quinoa, zucchini, yellow squash, lemon, herbs, olive oil, garlic, cherry tomatoes
recipe: 1. Season cod with herbs and lemon. 2. Bake cod at 400°F for 12-15 minutes. 3. Cook quinoa. 4. Sauté zucchini and squash with garlic. 5. Add cherry tomatoes at end. 6. Serve cod over quinoa and vegetables.

name: Protein-Packed Oatmeal
ingredients: Steel-cut oats, protein powder, almond milk, peanut butter, banana, chia seeds, cinnamon, maple syrup
recipe: 1. Cook oats with almond milk. 2. Stir in protein powder when oats are nearly done. 3. Add peanut butter and cinnamon. 4. Top with sliced banana and chia seeds. 5. Drizzle with small amount of maple syrup.

name: Chicken Tikka Masala Bowl
ingredients: Chicken breast, basmati rice, Greek yogurt, tomato sauce, garam masala, turmeric, ginger, garlic, onion
recipe: 1. Marinate chicken in yogurt and spices for 30 minutes. 2. Cook basmati rice. 3. Grill marinated chicken pieces. 4. Make tikka masala sauce with tomatoes and spices. 5. Combine chicken with sauce. 6. Serve over rice.

name: Mexican Protein Bowl
ingredients: Grilled chicken, black beans, brown rice, avocado, salsa, corn, bell peppers, lime, cilantro, Greek yogurt
recipe: 1. Cook brown rice with cilantro and lime. 2. Grill seasoned chicken breast. 3. Heat black beans with cumin. 4. Roast corn and bell peppers. 5. Assemble bowl with all ingredients. 6. Top with avocado, salsa, and Greek yogurt.

name: Shrimp and Cauliflower Rice Stir-Fry
ingredients: Large shrimp, cauliflower rice, snap peas, carrots, ginger, garlic, sesame oil, soy sauce, green onions
recipe: 1. Heat sesame oil in wok or large pan. 2. Sauté shrimp until pink and cooked through. 3. Add minced ginger and garlic. 4. Stir in cauliflower rice and vegetables. 5. Season with soy sauce. 6. Garnish with green onions.

name: Protein-Rich Chia Pudding
ingredients: Chia seeds, plant protein powder, almond milk, vanilla extract, maple syrup, fresh berries, almond butter
recipe: 1. Mix chia seeds with almond milk and let sit 10 minutes. 2. Blend in protein powder and vanilla. 3. Refrigerate overnight. 4. Top with berries and almond butter. 5. Drizzle with maple syrup if desired.

name: Bison Burger Lettuce Wraps
ingredients: Ground bison, butter lettuce, avocado, tomatoes, red onion, pickles, mustard, olive oil, herbs
recipe: 1. Season bison patties with herbs and spices. 2. Grill burgers to desired doneness. 3. Prepare lettuce cups and toppings. 4. Slice avocado and tomatoes. 5. Assemble burgers in lettuce wraps. 6. Serve with pickle spears.

name: Protein Smoothie Bowl
ingredients: Vanilla protein powder, frozen berries, banana, Greek yogurt, granola, coconut flakes, hemp seeds
recipe: 1. Blend protein powder, frozen berries, banana, and yogurt until thick. 2. Pour into bowl. 3. Top with granola, coconut flakes, and hemp seeds. 4. Add fresh fruit if desired. 5. Serve immediately.

name: Mediterranean Chicken Skewers
ingredients: Chicken thighs, red bell peppers, zucchini, red onion, olive oil, lemon, oregano, garlic, feta cheese
recipe: 1. Cut chicken and vegetables into chunks. 2. Marinate in olive oil, lemon, and herbs. 3. Thread onto skewers alternating chicken and vegetables. 4. Grill 12-15 minutes, turning frequently. 5. Serve with crumbled feta. 6. Garnish with fresh herbs.

name: High-Protein French Toast
ingredients: Whole grain bread, egg whites, whole eggs, protein powder, almond milk, cinnamon, vanilla, Greek yogurt, berries
recipe: 1. Whisk eggs, egg whites, protein powder, and almond milk. 2. Add cinnamon and vanilla to mixture. 3. Dip bread slices in egg mixture. 4. Cook in non-stick pan until golden. 5. Top with Greek yogurt and berries. 6. Serve warm.

name: Asian Lettuce Cups with Ground Turkey
ingredients: Ground turkey, butter lettuce, water chestnuts, mushrooms, ginger, garlic, soy sauce, sesame oil, green onions
recipe: 1. Cook ground turkey until browned and cooked through. 2. Add ginger, garlic, and mushrooms. 3. Stir in diced water chestnuts. 4. Season with soy sauce and sesame oil. 5. Serve in lettuce cups. 6. Garnish with green onions.

name: Protein Power Muffins
ingredients: Almond flour, protein powder, eggs, Greek yogurt, blueberries, baking powder, vanilla, stevia, almond milk
recipe: 1. Preheat oven to 350°F. 2. Mix dry ingredients in one bowl. 3. Combine wet ingredients in another bowl. 4. Fold wet into dry ingredients with blueberries. 5. Fill muffin cups and bake 18-20 minutes. 6. Cool before serving.

name: Moroccan Spiced Lamb with Vegetables
ingredients: Lamb shoulder, sweet potatoes, carrots, onions, cinnamon, cumin, ginger, turmeric, olive oil, almonds
recipe: 1. Season lamb with moroccan spices. 2. Sear lamb in dutch oven until browned. 3. Add vegetables and spices. 4. Add broth and simmer covered 25 minutes. 5. Garnish with toasted almonds. 6. Serve over cauliflower rice if desired.

name: Protein-Packed Breakfast Burrito
ingredients: Whole wheat tortilla, scrambled eggs, black beans, cheese, salsa, avocado, bell peppers, onions, Greek yogurt
recipe: 1. Scramble eggs with sautéed peppers and onions. 2. Warm black beans with cumin and garlic. 3. Warm tortilla in dry pan. 4. Layer eggs, beans, cheese in tortilla. 5. Add salsa and avocado. 6. Roll tightly and serve with Greek yogurt.

name: Thai Beef Salad
ingredients: Flank steak, mixed greens, cucumber, tomatoes, mint, cilantro, lime juice, fish sauce, chili peppers, peanuts
recipe: 1. Grill flank steak to medium-rare, let rest and slice thin. 2. Make dressing with lime juice, fish sauce, and chili. 3. Toss greens with cucumber and tomatoes. 4. Add sliced steak to salad. 5. Drizzle with dressing. 6. Garnish with herbs and peanuts.

name: Protein Ice Cream
ingredients: Frozen banana, vanilla protein powder, Greek yogurt, almond milk, vanilla extract, dark chocolate chips
recipe: 1. Blend frozen banana until it becomes creamy. 2. Add protein powder and Greek yogurt. 3. Pour in small amount of almond milk for consistency. 4. Add vanilla extract. 5. Fold in chocolate chips. 6. Serve immediately or freeze for firmer texture.

name: Italian Chicken Meatballs with Zucchini Noodles
ingredients: Ground chicken, zucchini, marinara sauce, parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic, egg, almond flour
recipe: 1. Mix ground chicken with egg, almond flour, and Italian herbs. 2. Form into meatballs and bake at 375°F for 20 minutes. 3. Spiralize zucchini into noodles. 4. Heat marinara sauce. 5. Sauté zucchini noodles briefly. 6. Serve meatballs over noodles with sauce and parmesan.

name: High-Protein Breakfast Quinoa Bowl
ingredients: Quinoa, almond milk, protein powder, banana, walnuts, cinnamon, vanilla, maple syrup, chia seeds
recipe: 1. Cook quinoa in almond milk until creamy. 2. Stir in protein powder while warm. 3. Add cinnamon and vanilla. 4. Top with sliced banana and walnuts. 5. Sprinkle with chia seeds. 6. Drizzle with maple syrup if desired.

name: Korean BBQ Pork Bowl
ingredients: Pork tenderloin, brown rice, kimchi, cucumber, sesame oil, soy sauce, ginger, garlic, sesame seeds
recipe: 1. Marinate sliced pork in soy sauce, ginger, and garlic. 2. Cook brown rice. 3. Stir-fry pork until cooked through. 4. Prepare cucumber salad with sesame oil. 5. Assemble bowl with rice, pork, kimchi, and cucumber. 6. Garnish with sesame seeds.

name: Chocolate Protein Energy Balls
ingredients: Chocolate protein powder, dates, almond butter, oats, chia seeds, coconut flakes, vanilla extract
recipe: 1. Soak dates in warm water until soft. 2. Blend dates, protein powder, and almond butter. 3. Mix in oats and chia seeds. 4. Add vanilla extract. 5. Roll into balls and coat with coconut. 6. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

name: Stuffed Bell Peppers with Turkey
ingredients: Bell peppers, ground turkey, cauliflower rice, onion, tomatoes, Italian herbs, garlic, olive oil, nutritional yeast
recipe: 1. Cut tops off bell peppers and remove seeds. 2. Cook ground turkey with onions and garlic. 3. Mix in cauliflower rice and diced tomatoes. 4. Season with Italian herbs. 5. Stuff peppers with mixture. 6. Bake covered at 375°F for 25 minutes.

name: Protein Pancake Stack
ingredients: Oat flour, vanilla protein powder, eggs, Greek yogurt, baking powder, almond milk, blueberries, sugar-free syrup
recipe: 1. Mix oat flour, protein powder, and baking powder. 2. Whisk eggs with Greek yogurt and almond milk. 3. Combine wet and dry ingredients. 4. Cook pancakes in non-stick pan. 5. Stack with blueberries between layers. 6. Top with sugar-free syrup.

name: Spanish Tuna and White Bean Salad
ingredients: Canned tuna, white beans, red onion, tomatoes, parsley, olive oil, lemon juice, capers, paprika
recipe: 1. Drain and flake tuna. 2. Rinse and drain white beans. 3. Dice red onion and tomatoes. 4. Make dressing with olive oil, lemon juice, and paprika. 5. Combine all ingredients. 6. Garnish with capers and fresh parsley.

name: Protein Cookie Dough Bites
ingredients: Vanilla protein powder, almond flour, almond butter, vanilla extract, stevia, mini dark chocolate chips, almond milk
recipe: 1. Mix protein powder and almond flour. 2. Add almond butter and vanilla extract. 3. Sweeten with stevia to taste. 4. Add small amount of almond milk for consistency. 5. Fold in chocolate chips. 6. Roll into bite-sized balls and chill.
